    <bioghist>
      <head>African American Newspapers</head>
      <p>Newspapers are a rich source for investigating the social,
         political, and economic activities in a community. African
         American Newspapers unlike their European American
         counterparts, they offer a unique insight into avenues often
         neglected by European American Publications.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>Political and Social activities, church news, ads,
         editorials from an African American perspective. African
         American newspapers have traditionally tried to fill in the
         information gap created by the majority news system. These
         papers provide a unique view of this perspective.</p>
      <p>There are some additional copies of Africian American
         newspapers located in the following manuscript groups: 1.
         James Hugo Johnston, Sr. Acc. # 1963-9 2. James Hugo Johnston,
         Jr. Acc. # 1963-10 3. Edna Meade Colson Acc. # 1965-13</p>
    </scopecontent>
